-CREATE TABLE:
Used to create table
Create table tablename (column_name1 datatype(size) constraints,column_name2 datatype(size) constraints....)
-ALTER TABLE:
Used to add a new columnn,modify the existing column, to inlcude or drop integrity constraint.
alter table tablename add/modify (attribute datatype(size));
-DROP TABLE
It will delete the table structure provided the table should be empty.
drop table table_name;
-TRUNCATE TABLE
If there is no further use of records stored in a table and the structure has to be retained
then the records (rows) alone can be deleted.
truncate table table_name;
-DESC
This is used to view the structure of the table.
desc table_name;
